comments: Nurkic (PHX) is still in possession of the ball when the shot clock expires.
Allen (PHX) reaches in and initiates contact to Reaves' (LAL) arm, affecting his ability to gather the ball.
Nurkic (PHX) reaches forwards and brushes Davis's (LAL) arm during the shot attempt and the contact is marginal.
James (LAL) remains established in the frontcourt upon receiving the pass and starting his dribble.
Davis (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and briefly dislodges it away from Nurkic (PHX), who recovers possession of the ball.  Any contact between the two players is incidental.
Durant (PHX) reaches across James's (LAL) left arm and initiates contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Nurkic (PHX) initiates contact to Davis's (LAL) right arm that affects his shot attempt at the rim.
Reddish (LAL) reaches in and across Booker's (PHX) body and affects his SQBR.  The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Davis (LAL) places a forearm against Durant's (PHX) body as he is trailing behind and the contact is marginal during the driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) steps to Reaves' (LAL) space, but Reaves loses his balance on his own and not as a result of any illegal contact initiated by Booker.
LAL is granted a timeout when Reaves (LAL) recovers the ball and pins it against his leg, before he loses it again.
Gordon (PHX) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
Prince (LAL) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Durant's (PHX) arm.
